WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.900 --> 00:00:14.630
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.630 --> 00:00:17.540
the tides of time,
and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.540 --> 00:00:20.370
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.370 --> 00:00:23.480
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:26.110
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.820 --> 00:00:41.040
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.080 --> 00:00:46.560
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.580 --> 00:00:52.100
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.440 --> 00:00:56.080
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:59.440 --> 00:01:02.700
I follow, follow in the footsteps

12
00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:05.990
of a dream that resembles no one

13
00:01:05.990 --> 00:01:09.220
Until I dramatically get it

14
00:01:18.080 --> 00:01:21.120
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

15
00:01:21.220 --> 00:01:24.200
of a dream no one can see

16
00:01:24.480 --> 00:01:30.220
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

17
00:01:30.460 --> 00:01:33.580
I don't really need everything to add up

18
00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:36.750
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

19
00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:40.350
run for paradise instead

20
00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:57.470
<b>Adventure on Little Garden</b>

21
00:02:12.530 --> 00:02:14.530
I wonder if it'll snow again.

22
00:02:14.530 --> 00:02:16.030
Why would it?

23
00:02:16.030 --> 00:02:19.200
It just does. You don't know
'cause you slept through it.

24
00:02:19.200 --> 00:02:20.450
Huh?

25
00:02:20.870 --> 00:02:23.250
Hey, do you think it'll snow again?

26
00:02:23.790 --> 00:02:28.250
It's a possibility, but that
first stretch of sea was special.

27
00:02:28.420 --> 00:02:33.130
The seven magnetic fields from
Reverse Mountain wreak havoc on it.

28
00:02:37.100 --> 00:02:39.890
However, you shouldn't
let down your guard here, either.

29
00:02:40.430 --> 00:02:43.980
Rarely is this sea as rough
as where we first set sail...

30
00:02:44.940 --> 00:02:48.400
but the fact remains: This sea is
much harsher than ordinary waters.

31
00:02:49.020 --> 00:02:51.070
Never underestimate these seas.

32
00:02:51.070 --> 00:02:52.400
That's the ironclad rule.

33
00:02:52.400 --> 00:02:54.200
Hey, guys!

34
00:02:55.070 --> 00:02:57.870
Wanna try a special drink I made?

35
00:02:59.030 --> 00:03:00.410
Yeah!

36
00:03:02.540 --> 00:03:04.250
Thanks!

37
00:03:08.710 --> 00:03:09.790
Hey, Usopp.

38
00:03:09.790 --> 00:03:11.460
Make us some fishing gear.

39
00:03:11.460 --> 00:03:13.720
Fishing, huh? You might
be on to something!

40
00:03:13.720 --> 00:03:14.800
Alright!

41
00:03:14.800 --> 00:03:17.890
I'll even make 'em
nice and stylish for you!

42
00:03:20.100 --> 00:03:21.970
Wow, you sure can put them away.

43
00:03:21.970 --> 00:03:23.350
So, is it any good?

44
00:03:27.190 --> 00:03:27.810
Awesome!

45
00:03:27.810 --> 00:03:29.650
Whoa! You're amazing, Karoo!

46
00:03:30.270 --> 00:03:32.110
How is any of this okay?!

47
00:03:32.110 --> 00:03:33.530
Here. For you.

48
00:03:33.530 --> 00:03:34.150
What?

49
00:03:35.030 --> 00:03:36.450
It'll be fine.

50
00:03:36.450 --> 00:03:40.280
They'll pick up the pace in a squall.

51
00:03:40.280 --> 00:03:41.870
They want to stay alive too.

52
00:03:42.830 --> 00:03:44.750
I suppose.

53
00:03:44.750 --> 00:03:46.330
They just seem so distracted.

54
00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:50.290
As long as you're on this ship,
you won't feel much stress.

55
00:03:54.460 --> 00:03:57.630
Attaboy! Go, go, go, go!

56
00:04:01.850 --> 00:04:03.810
Stupid Karoo!

57
00:04:10.270 --> 00:04:12.770
Yes, it is quite relaxing.

58
00:04:18.360 --> 00:04:19.820
Hey everyone, look!

59
00:04:19.820 --> 00:04:20.820
It's a dolphin!

60
00:04:21.240 --> 00:04:22.830
Whoa! He's cute!

61
00:04:33.800 --> 00:04:36.050
It's humongous!

62
00:04:48.270 --> 00:04:50.060
Get a move on!

63
00:04:52.020 --> 00:04:52.810
Let's go!

64
00:04:52.810 --> 00:04:54.440
– Okay!
– Yep!

65
00:04:59.110 --> 00:05:00.610
All right!

66
00:05:01.610 --> 00:05:02.530
Take that side!

67
00:05:02.530 --> 00:05:03.450
On it!

68
00:05:04.030 --> 00:05:05.080
Everyone...

69
00:05:05.080 --> 00:05:07.330
Unfurl the sails!

70
00:05:18.210 --> 00:05:19.010
Okay!

71
00:05:19.010 --> 00:05:21.380
Ride the wave
and lose that dolphin!

72
00:05:34.610 --> 00:05:37.280
Nami! What's our next heading?

73
00:05:37.280 --> 00:05:38.280
Hold on a sec.

74
00:05:38.280 --> 00:05:39.320
Let me check.

75
00:05:44.820 --> 00:05:46.530
Full turn aport!

76
00:05:49.250 --> 00:05:51.540
– Okay!
– Okay!

77
00:06:11.980 --> 00:06:13.190
There's no mistake.

78
00:06:13.810 --> 00:06:16.150
It's linked with Cactus Island.

79
00:06:16.150 --> 00:06:18.520
The next stop on our trip is...

80
00:06:19.190 --> 00:06:20.990
that island!

81
00:06:32.330 --> 00:06:34.080
There it is!

82
00:06:34.080 --> 00:06:36.960
Our second island in the Grand Line!

83
00:06:46.550 --> 00:06:50.600
<b>Vacation Island
The Grand Line</b>

84
00:06:55.310 --> 00:06:57.100
Mr. 3.

85
00:06:57.100 --> 00:06:58.440
What is it?

86
00:06:58.440 --> 00:06:59.980
A moment, please.

87
00:07:01.190 --> 00:07:05.070
No other tea can
compare to Earl Grey.

88
00:07:05.450 --> 00:07:06.610
I'm bored.

89
00:07:07.240 --> 00:07:11.290
You insist that you're bored,
yet you dislike work, right?

90
00:07:11.290 --> 00:07:11.870
Right.

91
00:07:11.870 --> 00:07:18.290
In that case, why not try
to enjoy this wondrous time off?

92
00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:24.260
Extended vacations are a privilege
afforded only to officer agents.

93
00:07:24.760 --> 00:07:26.260
Also,

94
00:07:26.300 --> 00:07:31.850
<b>Mr. 3
Officer Agent, Baroque Works</b>

95
00:07:26.760 --> 00:07:31.720
you mustn't refer to me
by my code name in public.

96
00:07:32.220 --> 00:07:36.060
People will discover that I'm Mr. 3.

97
00:07:38.270 --> 00:07:41.480
<b>Miss Golden Week
Officer Agent, Baroque Works</b>

98
00:07:38.600 --> 00:07:39.610
You think?

99
00:07:41.480 --> 00:07:46.450
By the way, you've been staring
at that piece of paper for days now.

100
00:07:46.780 --> 00:07:48.320
What ever could it be?

101
00:07:48.320 --> 00:07:50.120
An order from the boss.

102
00:07:50.990 --> 00:07:52.410
Why didn't you say so sooner?!

103
00:07:55.540 --> 00:07:58.460
Apparently, Mr. 5 was taken out.

104
00:07:59.210 --> 00:08:03.380
I would have preferred
seeing Mr. 2 get eliminated.

105
00:08:03.380 --> 00:08:06.380
Then you'd get a promotion, right?

106
00:08:06.880 --> 00:08:11.550
Mr. 5's defeat isn't worth
making a fuss over.

107
00:08:12.140 --> 00:08:18.060
Alas, he's simply a novice who
overestimated his status and abilities.

108
00:08:18.690 --> 00:08:22.190
No matter how amazing
the devil fruit power one gains,

109
00:08:22.190 --> 00:08:27.700
if one can't properly utilize it,
that person's existence is wasted.

110
00:08:32.490 --> 00:08:39.040
Only the most superb minds
execute the most superb crimes.

111
00:08:39.040 --> 00:08:43.040
To whomever took him out,
why don't we reveal

112
00:08:43.040 --> 00:08:48.720
the terror that comes from defying
this criminal organization?

113
00:08:59.890 --> 00:09:02.690
So this is Little Garden!

114
00:09:02.690 --> 00:09:04.270
What's "little" about it?

115
00:09:04.820 --> 00:09:08.030
This place doesn't
quite fit its cute name.

116
00:09:09.150 --> 00:09:11.360
I-It's like an uncharted island.

117
00:09:11.360 --> 00:09:12.990
The jungle's so thick!

118
00:09:12.990 --> 00:09:15.030
We'll need to be careful.

119
00:09:15.030 --> 00:09:18.410
I'm worried about what
Miss All-Sunday was saying.

120
00:09:18.870 --> 00:09:22.250
L-L-Like a monster might show up?!

121
00:09:22.250 --> 00:09:23.580
Who knows?

122
00:09:23.580 --> 00:09:27.210
Then at this next stop,
let's stay aboard the ship!

123
00:09:27.210 --> 00:09:30.090
Y'know, the log could
take a while to register.

124
00:09:30.090 --> 00:09:33.180
Also, we have to
stock up on food soon.

125
00:09:33.510 --> 00:09:36.180
We didn't get anything
from that last town.

126
00:09:36.470 --> 00:09:38.390
There's a river over there!

127
00:09:39.270 --> 00:09:40.640
– What?
– Really?

128
00:09:45.610 --> 00:09:47.440
I hope there's a barbecue restaurant.

129
00:09:47.440 --> 00:09:48.900
As if there'd be one!

130
00:09:48.900 --> 00:09:51.360
What happened to
stocking up on food?

131
00:09:51.360 --> 00:09:53.280
We'll collect food to cook later!

132
00:09:53.280 --> 00:09:55.700
Honestly! You got a screw loose?

133
00:09:55.700 --> 00:09:57.580
But it's dangerous to go ashore.

134
00:10:00.450 --> 00:10:03.210
For starters,
take a look at these plants.

135
00:10:03.210 --> 00:10:05.540
I've never seen those
in any encyclopedia.

136
00:10:12.220 --> 00:10:13.880
You're so cute!

137
00:10:14.640 --> 00:10:15.390
You mean me?

138
00:10:15.390 --> 00:10:18.060
Obviously I meant Nami!

139
00:10:18.060 --> 00:10:19.850
What was that just now?

140
00:10:21.850 --> 00:10:23.230
It's all right.

141
00:10:23.230 --> 00:10:24.520
It's just a bird.

142
00:10:24.520 --> 00:10:26.360
And this is just a jungle.

143
00:10:26.360 --> 00:10:27.310
Don't worry.

144
00:10:30.070 --> 00:10:31.070
What's the matter?

145
00:10:37.240 --> 00:10:39.290
What's your problem,
you damn bird?!

146
00:10:39.950 --> 00:10:42.250
A lizard? I wonder if it tastes good.

147
00:10:46.880 --> 00:10:50.550
Do jungles normally
make that kind of noise?

148
00:10:51.130 --> 00:10:55.180
That sounded like a volcano!

149
00:11:07.900 --> 00:11:08.900
A tiger?!

150
00:11:09.610 --> 00:11:10.440
It's way too big!

151
00:11:20.580 --> 00:11:21.740
What...?!

152
00:11:21.740 --> 00:11:23.540
What happened to it?!

153
00:11:23.540 --> 00:11:26.040
This isn't normal!
This is definitely not normal!

154
00:11:26.790 --> 00:11:30.380
Why would a tiger, king of the jungle,
collapse in a bloody heap?!

155
00:11:33.380 --> 00:11:36.340
It's decided that we're
not going ashore!

156
00:11:37.640 --> 00:11:40.680
We'll wait quietly on the ship,
and when the log is ready...

157
00:11:40.680 --> 00:11:41.180
Right!

158
00:11:41.180 --> 00:11:43.600
...we leave this island immediately.

159
00:11:43.600 --> 00:11:44.560
Right!

160
00:11:44.560 --> 00:11:47.650
W-We're in a hurry
to get to Alabasta.

161
00:11:57.360 --> 00:11:59.240
Sanji! Lunch!

162
00:11:59.240 --> 00:11:59.950
Lunch?

163
00:12:00.660 --> 00:12:02.700
Yeah! To restore my energy!

164
00:12:02.700 --> 00:12:06.290
A pirate lunch with
lots of meat and no veggies!

165
00:12:06.290 --> 00:12:07.920
I smell adventure!

166
00:12:08.670 --> 00:12:11.210
W-Wait a sec!

167
00:12:11.210 --> 00:12:12.380
Where are you going?!

168
00:12:12.380 --> 00:12:14.260
Adventure!

169
00:12:14.260 --> 00:12:16.670
Wanna come along?
Adventure! Adventure!

170
00:12:17.260 --> 00:12:20.340
It's no use. You can't stop him
when he gets this enthusiastic.

171
00:12:21.140 --> 00:12:22.810
No way!

172
00:12:22.810 --> 00:12:26.310
Somewhere in here is a monster
that beats up huge tigers!

173
00:12:26.310 --> 00:12:28.600
Sanji! Lunch!

174
00:12:28.600 --> 00:12:29.850
You got it.

175
00:12:29.850 --> 00:12:31.270
Coming right up.

176
00:12:34.400 --> 00:12:36.940
Say, do you mind if I come along?

177
00:12:36.940 --> 00:12:37.780
What?!

178
00:12:37.780 --> 00:12:39.360
Sure! C'mon! C'mon!

179
00:12:39.360 --> 00:12:41.280
Not you too!

180
00:12:41.700 --> 00:12:42.700
Indeed.

181
00:12:42.700 --> 00:12:45.700
If I stay here,
I might begin to brood.

182
00:12:45.700 --> 00:12:48.210
Exploring will distract me
until the log sets.

183
00:12:48.210 --> 00:12:49.040
No way!

184
00:12:49.040 --> 00:12:51.880
Luffy going is one thing,
but it's too risky for you!

185
00:12:52.380 --> 00:12:54.500
I'll be fine. I'll have Karoo by my side.

186
00:12:57.840 --> 00:13:01.550
His face tells
a different story, though.

187
00:13:01.550 --> 00:13:04.510
Then Vivi gets a sweetheart lunch.

188
00:13:05.140 --> 00:13:07.980
Could you also prepare
a drink for Karoo?

189
00:13:07.980 --> 00:13:09.100
Of course!

190
00:13:09.100 --> 00:13:10.850
Leave it to me!

191
00:13:16.530 --> 00:13:17.650
Okay.

192
00:13:23.410 --> 00:13:27.750
So! That's two pirate lunches
and a very special drink for Karoo.

193
00:13:27.750 --> 00:13:29.040
You're all set.

194
00:13:29.040 --> 00:13:30.040
Okay!

195
00:13:34.920 --> 00:13:37.250
Well, then. See you later!

196
00:13:37.250 --> 00:13:39.050
All right! Let's go!

197
00:13:39.050 --> 00:13:41.050
We'll be back in a little while!

198
00:13:42.760 --> 00:13:46.180
Miss Wednesday sure is brave.

199
00:13:46.180 --> 00:13:49.220
She did infiltrate an enemy
organization, after all.

200
00:13:52.230 --> 00:13:55.110
Well, I'm bored too.
I'm going for a walk.

201
00:13:55.110 --> 00:13:56.070
A walk?!

202
00:13:59.360 --> 00:14:00.490
Hey, Zoro!

203
00:14:01.110 --> 00:14:02.280
Wait!

204
00:14:03.610 --> 00:14:05.490
We're short on food.

205
00:14:05.490 --> 00:14:08.080
If you see an animal that
looks edible, bring it back.

206
00:14:08.450 --> 00:14:10.290
Okay, got it.

207
00:14:10.290 --> 00:14:14.580
I'll find one that you
couldn't possibly capture.

208
00:14:14.580 --> 00:14:15.920
Hold it right there!

209
00:14:16.460 --> 00:14:17.420
Huh?!

210
00:14:18.090 --> 00:14:20.510
I can't just let that challenge slide!

211
00:14:20.510 --> 00:14:25.050
So you think you can
nab a bigger one than me?

212
00:14:25.890 --> 00:14:27.140
Of course!

213
00:14:32.980 --> 00:14:34.100
You're on, then!

214
00:14:38.070 --> 00:14:40.940
Look! He who collects
the most kilograms of meat wins.

215
00:14:41.530 --> 00:14:43.400
Don't you mean to say tons?

216
00:14:43.820 --> 00:14:46.410
Save the attitude for when
you've caught something.

217
00:14:47.030 --> 00:14:48.530
Sounds fair to me!

218
00:14:50.160 --> 00:14:53.750
I wonder. Why do they
all turn out this way?

219
00:14:53.750 --> 00:14:55.710
I know how you feel.

220
00:14:55.710 --> 00:14:58.380
No need to cry.
I'm with you on this.

221
00:15:04.380 --> 00:15:05.380
I'm screwed.

222
00:15:05.380 --> 00:15:07.550
Hey! That's my line!

223
00:15:12.180 --> 00:15:13.600
But wait a sec.

224
00:15:14.440 --> 00:15:16.150
Huh? Wh-Wh-What's the matter?!

225
00:15:18.190 --> 00:15:20.110
N-N-N-Nami?!

226
00:15:20.110 --> 00:15:21.980
This isn't it.

227
00:15:21.980 --> 00:15:23.070
This isn't it, either.

228
00:15:23.070 --> 00:15:25.490
Ouch! Ow, ow! H-Hey, Nami!

229
00:15:25.490 --> 00:15:28.370
Nami! Hey! What the heck
are you looking for?

230
00:15:28.370 --> 00:15:30.950
I remember reading about it in a book.

231
00:15:31.450 --> 00:15:33.540
About... About what?

232
00:15:33.540 --> 00:15:34.870
Little Garden.

233
00:15:34.870 --> 00:15:36.580
Whoa!

234
00:15:38.540 --> 00:15:39.540
What is it?

235
00:15:39.540 --> 00:15:40.790
Here, look at this!

236
00:15:41.210 --> 00:15:43.300
There's a shellfish, but it's like a squid.

237
00:15:47.220 --> 00:15:48.140
A squid shellfish!

238
00:15:49.090 --> 00:15:52.180
It looks a lot like an ammonite.

239
00:15:52.180 --> 00:15:53.140
So, a squid shellfish?

240
00:16:05.490 --> 00:16:08.780
Why do I get the feeling
I'm being followed?

241
00:16:08.780 --> 00:16:10.070
Just my imagination.

242
00:16:25.420 --> 00:16:26.590
Whoa there!

243
00:16:26.590 --> 00:16:29.010
Don't screw with me!

244
00:16:29.840 --> 00:16:32.390
Collier Shoot!

245
00:16:44.360 --> 00:16:46.320
What the hell is this...?

246
00:16:46.320 --> 00:16:47.740
Is it edible?

247
00:16:49.860 --> 00:16:51.320
Let me see...

248
00:16:51.320 --> 00:16:52.570
Which one was it?

249
00:16:53.280 --> 00:16:56.410
I swear I read it recently,
but it must have slipped my mind.

250
00:17:03.670 --> 00:17:04.590
Hey...

251
00:17:04.590 --> 00:17:07.050
Why is there a sea king on land?

252
00:17:11.640 --> 00:17:12.970
A dinosaur!

253
00:17:12.970 --> 00:17:14.220
A dinosaur?!

254
00:17:14.600 --> 00:17:17.430
Then, this is a prehistoric island!

255
00:17:17.430 --> 00:17:18.180
Huh?

256
00:17:18.450 --> 00:17:22.150
This island hasn't progressed
past the time of the dinosaurs!

257
00:17:22.550 --> 00:17:23.300
Hm?

258
00:17:24.520 --> 00:17:28.860
Trade and culture exchange
on the Grand Line is very rare,

259
00:17:28.860 --> 00:17:31.490
due to the harshness
of sea travel here.

260
00:17:31.490 --> 00:17:34.660
Thus, each island establishes
its own unique culture.

261
00:17:35.830 --> 00:17:39.080
Some islands have
become incredibly advanced,

262
00:17:40.750 --> 00:17:43.250
and there are others
that remain unchanged,

263
00:17:43.250 --> 00:17:47.340
their progress halted for thousands,
no, tens of thousands of years.

264
00:17:50.510 --> 00:17:54.720
It's all thanks to the Grand Line's
nonsensical climate.

265
00:17:55.180 --> 00:18:00.060
That is why this island is stuck
in the age of the dinosaurs.

266
00:18:00.680 --> 00:18:02.890
Amazing!

267
00:18:02.890 --> 00:18:03.690
Luffy!

268
00:18:07.360 --> 00:18:09.150
Don't leap to it!

269
00:18:11.150 --> 00:18:12.990
Usopp!

270
00:18:12.990 --> 00:18:15.780
Huh? What? What's the matter?

271
00:18:15.780 --> 00:18:17.740
Did you find the book?

272
00:18:18.740 --> 00:18:19.660
Yeah.

273
00:18:29.960 --> 00:18:31.010
This is bad.

274
00:18:31.010 --> 00:18:32.220
On this island...

275
00:18:55.030 --> 00:18:55.990
What?

276
00:18:56.820 --> 00:18:59.450
It felt like Nami
just called out to me.

277
00:19:03.370 --> 00:19:08.920
To those residing here,
this island is naught but a little garden.

278
00:19:10.380 --> 00:19:11.550
Little Garden...

279
00:19:12.590 --> 00:19:14.720
is what I shall name this place.

280
00:19:15.720 --> 00:19:18.100
Louis Arnote, Explorer.

281
00:19:33.150 --> 00:19:34.190
So?

282
00:19:33.530 --> 00:19:36.700
<b>Brogy the Giant</b>

283
00:19:35.610 --> 00:19:36.700
What do you say?

284
00:19:37.450 --> 00:19:39.070
Wh-What was that?

285
00:19:39.070 --> 00:19:41.870
C-Could you repeat that?

286
00:19:43.290 --> 00:19:45.830
I asked if you have any booze.

287
00:19:47.580 --> 00:19:48.670
We don't have much left...

288
00:19:49.040 --> 00:19:51.210
So then, you do have some!

289
00:19:51.210 --> 00:19:55.630
Wh-What we have isn't for drinking,
just cooking and disinfecting.

290
00:19:55.630 --> 00:19:58.840
But if you'd like, you can have it all.

291
00:20:06.230 --> 00:20:07.390
Dino...

292
00:20:07.390 --> 00:20:08.560
Dinosaur?

293
00:20:23.790 --> 00:20:28.960
I'm Brogy, Elbaph's strongest warrior!

294
00:20:34.710 --> 00:20:36.340
Now I've got meat.

295
00:20:36.340 --> 00:20:38.340
Allow me to treat you as my guests.

296
00:20:43.970 --> 00:20:45.470
H-Hey.

297
00:20:46.100 --> 00:20:49.980
P-Pretend we're dead,
n-no matter what happens.

298
00:20:49.980 --> 00:20:54.020
D-Doesn't pretending to be dead
only work on b-bears?

299
00:21:02.620 --> 00:21:04.790
Whoa!

300
00:21:04.790 --> 00:21:07.910
What a great view!

301
00:21:08.410 --> 00:21:10.830
I wanna have my lunch up here.

302
00:21:11.420 --> 00:21:14.800
Th-This is not
the time for idle chatter!

303
00:21:17.170 --> 00:21:19.550
So there really are volcanoes.

304
00:21:19.880 --> 00:21:23.550
And there's a mountain
with huge holes as well.

305
00:21:25.310 --> 00:21:26.390
It's dangerous!

306
00:21:26.390 --> 00:21:28.060
Come down already!

307
00:21:37.110 --> 00:21:39.650
He's been eaten!

308
00:21:41.490 --> 00:21:43.160
Where am I?

309
00:22:23.110 --> 00:22:24.570
Whoa...!

310
00:22:25.370 --> 00:22:31.960
<b>Dorry the Giant</b>

311
00:22:27.330 --> 00:22:28.620
I was watching.

312
00:22:28.620 --> 00:22:31.870
Grappling longnecks in the jungle...

313
00:22:31.870 --> 00:22:33.790
What a lively human!

314
00:22:33.790 --> 00:22:35.920
You're my first guest in a long time.

315
00:22:36.290 --> 00:22:38.880
You're huge! Are you a human?

316
00:22:41.420 --> 00:22:45.340
I'm Dorry, Elbaph's strongest warrior!

317
00:22:48.720 --> 00:22:50.770
A... A giant!

318
00:22:51.520 --> 00:22:55.190
I've heard of them, but this is my
first time actually seeing one.

319
00:22:56.310 --> 00:22:58.480
I'm Luffy. I'm a pirate.

320
00:23:00.440 --> 00:23:02.940
A pirate?! Good for you!

321
00:23:04.400 --> 00:23:05.910
Karoo! Wake up!

322
00:23:05.910 --> 00:23:07.450
Let's run while we can!

323
00:23:07.990 --> 00:23:11.410
Oh yeah, those two over there
are Vivi and Karoo. Nice to meet you!

324
00:23:12.200 --> 00:23:14.790
Luffy just had
to open his big mouth.

325
00:23:17.630 --> 00:23:20.340
Let me invite you to my place!

326
00:23:20.380 --> 00:23:25.510
<b>Home of Brogy the Giant</b>

327
00:23:42.110 --> 00:23:43.530
Now, eat!

328
00:23:43.530 --> 00:23:45.860
Dinosaur meat is tasty.

329
00:23:48.370 --> 00:23:50.780
I-I'm not hungry.

330
00:23:51.370 --> 00:23:53.450
Don't hold back!

331
00:23:55.290 --> 00:23:57.460
– I don't want to eat...
– I don't want to eat...

332
00:23:58.960 --> 00:24:02.710
But dinosaur meat is
real tasty. I'm tellin' you.

333
00:24:03.840 --> 00:24:07.090
Is he gonna make us
eat the dinosaur meat...

334
00:24:07.090 --> 00:24:08.800
...just to fatten us up a bit...

335
00:24:08.800 --> 00:24:10.720
...and then eat us?

336
00:24:10.720 --> 00:24:13.220
Yup. This is textbook giant, all right.

337
00:24:13.600 --> 00:24:16.020
But we're still so young.

338
00:24:16.020 --> 00:24:17.640
Then maybe we're at peak flavor.

339
00:24:17.640 --> 00:24:20.360
What a waste.

340
00:24:20.360 --> 00:24:22.820
It's good, I'm tellin' you...

341
00:24:24.360 --> 00:24:27.530
If we manage to fast
until the log is registered,

342
00:24:27.530 --> 00:24:29.610
we might stay thin enough to survive.

343
00:24:29.610 --> 00:24:33.410
But how long will it take
for the log to finish?

344
00:24:33.410 --> 00:24:39.540
After a three-day fast, I'll succumb
to this meat's amazing aroma.

345
00:24:39.540 --> 00:24:43.630
Brogy, can I ask you a question?

346
00:24:45.130 --> 00:24:46.970
What is it, little miss?

347
00:24:46.970 --> 00:24:50.510
H-How long will it take
for this island's log to register?

348
00:24:51.640 --> 00:24:52.510
One year.

349
00:24:52.510 --> 00:24:53.720
– What?!
– What?!

350
00:24:55.470 --> 00:25:00.690
Oh no... There's no way
we can fast for a year...!

351
00:25:01.230 --> 00:25:03.650
I... definitely won't keep from eating.

352
00:25:03.650 --> 00:25:06.320
Well, make yourselves at home!

353
00:25:18.370 --> 00:25:23.330
<b>Home of Dorry the Giant</b>

354
00:25:19.000 --> 00:25:21.750
This is yummy, giant old guy!

355
00:25:21.750 --> 00:25:25.130
That "pirate lunch" of yours was, too,

356
00:25:25.130 --> 00:25:27.630
though it was a little small for me.

357
00:25:28.970 --> 00:25:30.800
You bet it's good!

358
00:25:30.800 --> 00:25:34.350
That's a special lunch the chef
on my pirate ship made.

359
00:25:34.350 --> 00:25:36.260
Badmouth it, and I'll beat you up.

360
00:25:37.060 --> 00:25:39.100
Beat me up, you say?

361
00:25:42.190 --> 00:25:44.690
You're a riot, kid!

362
00:25:44.690 --> 00:25:46.780
Th-They're becoming awfully friendly.

363
00:25:47.440 --> 00:25:50.740
By the way, why are you
living here alone, old guy?

364
00:25:51.400 --> 00:25:53.410
Isn't there a village or something?

365
00:25:52.740 --> 00:25:53.410
Huh?

366
00:25:53.870 --> 00:25:55.490
There is a village.

367
00:25:55.490 --> 00:25:57.490
It's a warriors' village called Elbaph.

368
00:25:57.490 --> 00:26:00.580
It's elsewhere in the Grand Line.

369
00:26:01.120 --> 00:26:03.580
But there are rules in the village.

370
00:26:04.920 --> 00:26:05.590
Rules?

371
00:26:05.590 --> 00:26:10.050
For example, if a fight breaks out
and neither party concedes,

372
00:26:10.050 --> 00:26:13.300
the gods of Elbaph intercede
with their judgment.

373
00:26:13.300 --> 00:26:16.640
Elbaph's gods favor one party
with divine protection in battle,

374
00:26:16.640 --> 00:26:18.810
and thus the victor is deemed correct.

375
00:26:19.640 --> 00:26:21.520
Elbaph's gods, huh?

376
00:26:21.980 --> 00:26:24.600
I once started such a fight,

377
00:26:24.600 --> 00:26:28.940
and now this island hosts a duel
between another man and me.

378
00:26:28.940 --> 00:26:32.200
One of us will survive,
so that man will be correct.

379
00:26:33.610 --> 00:26:36.950
But even after 100 years,
the matter still isn't settled!

380
00:26:37.950 --> 00:26:40.290
You guys have been fighting
for 100 years?!

381
00:26:41.000 --> 00:26:43.250
No surprise there.

382
00:26:43.250 --> 00:26:47.500
Our lifespan is at least
three times as long as yours.

383
00:26:49.300 --> 00:26:51.090
Three times or otherwise,

384
00:26:51.090 --> 00:26:53.840
wouldn't the fighting
wane after 100 years?

385
00:26:54.380 --> 00:26:56.760
Why would you
carry on for so long?!

386
00:26:56.760 --> 00:26:58.430
It's a duel to the death, right?!

387
00:27:06.100 --> 00:27:07.980
Whoa!

388
00:27:08.440 --> 00:27:10.480
That's a huge eruption!

389
00:27:10.900 --> 00:27:13.240
Well, time to go.

390
00:27:13.740 --> 00:27:14.280
Huh?

391
00:27:21.660 --> 00:27:22.910
What's that?

392
00:27:22.910 --> 00:27:24.290
An eruption...

393
00:27:27.790 --> 00:27:28.330
Huh?

394
00:27:28.330 --> 00:27:29.250
Wha...?

395
00:27:32.300 --> 00:27:35.180
He suddenly got so serious.

396
00:27:35.630 --> 00:27:39.850
Sorry, I have to head out for a bit.

397
00:27:39.850 --> 00:27:42.270
What? Head out?

398
00:27:42.270 --> 00:27:43.520
Yes.

399
00:27:44.060 --> 00:27:47.730
That was the signal for me
to continue my 100-year duel.

400
00:27:47.730 --> 00:27:49.110
A duel?

401
00:27:49.110 --> 00:27:52.280
W-With whom? Where?!
And for what reason?!

402
00:27:52.280 --> 00:27:53.690
Reason?

403
00:27:54.110 --> 00:27:55.400
I don't remember.

404
00:27:59.030 --> 00:28:01.620
Before we realized it,
it had become routine.

405
00:28:02.410 --> 00:28:06.080
The eruption of the central mountain
is the signal for the duel.

406
00:28:07.000 --> 00:28:08.170
What?!

407
00:28:08.170 --> 00:28:11.790
Locked in a death match
for 100 years, and with such hatred...

408
00:28:12.300 --> 00:28:14.760
What in the world caused this fight?!

409
00:28:15.130 --> 00:28:16.130
Stop it.

410
00:28:17.380 --> 00:28:19.050
It's not like that.

411
00:28:26.480 --> 00:28:28.480
Right. It's a matter of pride!

412
00:28:37.240 --> 00:28:39.660
I forgot the reason...

413
00:28:41.660 --> 00:28:44.200
a long time ago!
